With incorporation of virtual layer, the infectivity probability (denoted by βAB) for intra-community infection is related with the state of corresponding node for the investigated susceptible individual on the virtual layer. This is due to the reason that if the susceptible individual is aware of the epidemic, then he or she is likely to take preventive measures i.e., self-protection. Hence, for a susceptible individual in community A with an infected neighbor in community B (i.e., SPA
IPB), if he or she is unware of the epidemic (i.e., scenario (a) in Fig. 3
), then it is likely to be infected with a probability of βAB; otherwise, corresponding state combination remains with a probability of 1−βAB. Nevertheless, if the susceptible individual is aware of the epidemic (as depicted by Fig. 3(b)), then the infection probability is to be reduced with a factor of γAB (0 ≤ γAB ≤ 1) (i.e., corresponding infectivity probability equals to γABβAB). Otherwise, the state combination of SPAIPB remains with a probability of 1−γABβAB. For the state combination of IPASPB, similar analysis can be performed.
